{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In our approach, each word (or token) in the text undergoes partsof-speech (POS) tagging and named entity recognition (NER).",
    "For executing various NLP tasks, such as tokenization, tagging, lemmatization and parsing, we utilized the SpaCy [23] Python library, capitalizing on its pre-trained model (en_core_web_sm-3.7.0), matcher APIs, and visualization tools.",
    "Subsequently, a grammatical dependency tag is attached to each token by SpaCy, creating what is termed as \"dependency tree\".",
    "An example of such a dependency diagram is presented in Fig.",
    "S1A, Additional file 1."
  ],
